    "export_view": {
      "value": "<h3 id=\"IntegratedPayments:TroubleshootingResources-WiredConnectionforBluefinDevices\">Wired Connection for Bluefin Devices</h3><p>For consistent connectivity with your payment device(s), we recommend that your computer and PAX device be connected to your router with an ethernet cable. Wireless connections are less reliable for communicating with the PAX S300 and could result in sudden connection failures.</p><h3 id=\"IntegratedPayments:TroubleshootingResources-WirelessConnectionforBluefinDevices\">Wireless Connection for Bluefin Devices</h3><p>If using a dual-band Wi-Fi router, the 2.4GHz connection is more reliable for data transmission.</p><h3 id=\"IntegratedPayments:TroubleshootingResources-NetworkSwitches\">Network Switches</h3><p>Many network switches will stop the DHCP process from happening and will not assign an IP address to the PAX device. For this reason, we highly recommend that the PAX device be plugged directly into your router.</p><h3 id=\"IntegratedPayments:TroubleshootingResources-BluefinIntegratedPaymentStatus\">Bluefin Integrated Payment Status</h3><p>Bluefin users can subscribe to updates to be notified of any processing issues and outages at <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://status.bluefin.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://status.bluefin.com/</a>.</p><h3 id=\"IntegratedPayments:TroubleshootingResources-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934295157/Integrated+Payment+Processing+-+Start+Here\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934295157\" data-linked-resource-version=\"9\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Integrated Payment Processing - Start Here!</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934229721/image-20230622-173939.png?api=v2\"></span><p><strong>If you are experiencing connectivity errors when initiating a transaction:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Make sure the PAX device is on the Bluefin home screen. The device may be unresponsive to requests when viewing the Settings menu or the app is running in the background.</p></li><li><p>Confirm that the<a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934197020/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Update+Your+IP+Address+in+RepairQ\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934197020\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\"> IP address</a> and port (10009) were entered properly.</p></li><li><p>Update your DNS Server Settings.</p></li><li><p>Verify the device <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934786687/Integrated+Payments+Setup+PAX+Security+Certificate+Installation+and+Testing\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934786687\" data-linked-resource-version=\"12\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Security Certificate is installed</a> on your computer.</p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934786757/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Ping+Your+Device+to+See+if+it+is+Reachable\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934786757\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Ping the device</a> to verify your computer can reach it over the local network.</p></li><li><p>Verify the device is configured to communicate with RepairQ</p></li><li><p>Verify the PAX device has the latest update installed. Bluefin support can assist with this.\u00a0</p><ul><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://www.bluefin.com/support/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bluefin Support Website</a></p></li></ul></li><li><p>Verify the device is configured to communicate with RepairQ</p></li></ul><p><strong>See the following for a list of errors and how to resolve them:</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>CARD DATA UNDREADABLE</strong> - This could mean your device is not configured properly for your merchant account. Contact Bluefin Support for help configuring your device.</p><ul><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://www.bluefin.com/support/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bluefin Support Website</a></p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Token ID Not Found</strong> - Double-check that you have the right Bluefin Account ID and API Key in your integration settings for the testing location. If those are correct, contact Bluefin Support for further assistance.</p></li><li><p><strong>Invalid Group</strong> - The Merchant Account ID field on the location settings page is invalid. Double-check that the Account ID matches the location, and make sure you have the right <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934786847/Integrated+Payments+Setup+Adding+Bluefin+Credentials+in+RepairQ\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934786847\" data-linked-resource-version=\"11\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Account ID and API configured in the Bluefin settings</a>.</p></li><li><p><strong>Duplicate Transactions</strong> - This could mean that you have connectivity issues causing the device to re-submit data during an interruption in service. There are also settings to block duplicate transaction attempts on the device and at the gateway level. We recommend<a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://www.bluefin.com/download/product/payconex/user-guide/Content/Contacting%20Support.htm\" rel=\"nofollow\"> contacting Bluefin Support</a> for instructions on how to turn on these features for your payment gateway.</p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934229721/image-20230622-173941.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"IntegratedPayments:TroubleshootingResources-SecurityCertificateInstallation\">Security Certificate Installation</h2><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934786687/Integrated+Payments+Setup+PAX+Security+Certificate+Installation+and+Testing\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934786687\" data-linked-resource-version=\"12\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Integrated Payments Setup: PAX Security Certificate Installation</a></p><h2 id=\"IntegratedPayments:TroubleshootingResources-Transactions\">Transactions</h2><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1935769605/Integrated+Payments+Setup+Performing+a+Test+Transaction+with+a+PAX+Terminal+Device\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1935769605\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Integrated Payments Setup: Performing a Test Transaction with a PAX Terminal Device</a></p><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1937014916/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Invalid+Credit+Card+Entry\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1937014916\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PAX Device Troubleshooting: Invalid Credit Card Entry</a></p><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1938161692/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Duplicate+Payment+Requests\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1938161692\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PAX Device Troubleshooting: Duplicate Payment Requests</a></p><h2 id=\"IntegratedPayments:TroubleshootingResources-IPAddressManagement/PingingYourDevicefromaComputer\">IP Address Management/Pinging Your Device from a Computer</h2><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934917880/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Find+the+IP+Address+Assigned+to+Your+PAX+S300\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934917880\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PAX Device Troubleshooting: Find the IP Address Assigned to Your Bluefin PAX S300</a></p><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934196946/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Find+the+IP+Address+Assigned+to+Your+Bluefin+PAX+A80+A920\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934196946\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PAX Device Troubleshooting: Find the IP Address Assigned to Your Bluefin PAX A80</a></p><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934196978/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Find+the+IP+Address+Assigned+to+Your+Bluefin+PAX+D210\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934196978\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PAX Device Troubleshooting: Find the IP Address Assigned to Your Bluefin PAX D210</a></p><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934197020/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Update+Your+IP+Address+in+RepairQ\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934197020\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PAX Device Troubleshooting: Update Your IP Address in RepairQ</a></p><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934786757/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Ping+Your+Device+to+See+if+it+is+Reachable\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934786757\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PAX Device Troubleshooting: Ping Your Device to See if it is Reachable</a></p><h2 id=\"IntegratedPayments:TroubleshootingResources-LANTypeManagement\">LAN Type Management</h2><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1935441921/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Change+the+LAN+Type+on+a+PAX+S300\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1935441921\" data-linked-resource-version=\"11\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PAX Device Troubleshooting: Change the LAN Type on a Bluefin PAX S300</a></p><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1935572993/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Change+the+LAN+Type+on+a+Bluefin+PAX+A80+A920\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1935572993\" data-linked-resource-version=\"9\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PAX Device Troubleshooting: Change the LAN Type on a Bluefin PAX A80</a></p><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1935179789/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Change+the+LAN+Type+on+a+Bluefin+PAX+D210\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1935179789\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PAX Device Troubleshooting: Change the LAN Type on a Bluefin PAX D210</a></p><h2 id=\"IntegratedPayments:TroubleshootingResources-DNSServerSettings\">DNS Server Settings</h2><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934197007/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Change+Your+DNS+Servers+-+macOS\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934197007\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PAX Device Troubleshooting: Change Your DNS Servers - macOS</a></p><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934295273/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Change+Your+DNS+Servers+-+macOS+Ventura\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934295273\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PAX Device Troubleshooting: Change Your DNS Servers - macOS Ventura</a></p><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934786834/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Change+Your+DNS+Servers+-+Windows+10\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934786834\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PAX Device Troubleshooting: Change Your DNS Servers - Windows 10</a></p><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/2068807721/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Change+Your+DNS+Servers+-+Windows+11\" data-linked-resource-id=\"2068807721\" data-linked-resource-version=\"2\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">PAX Device Troubleshooting: Change Your DNS Servers - Windows 11</a></p>",
